  "doc_id": "48293",
  "text": "The acquisition of nicotine IVSA in the present study seemed to occur rapidly, because steady levels of nicotine intake were achieved within 5 days of nicotine IVSA. The acquisition of nicotine IVSA also occurred in the first hour of nicotine access, because rats exhibited an increase in intake in the first hour of the first five sessions. Previous acquisition curves for extended nicotine IVSA reflect an initial increase in total nicotine intake across the first 5 to 10 days [CITATION_1] . However, the present study involved lever habituation for 5 days before nicotine access, and this procedure may account for the more rapid acquisition of stable nicotine self-administration in the present study.",
